U.K. Gilts Reverse Decline After Bank of England Minutes Release

-- B y   M a r k   M c C o r d
-- 
2011-09-21T08:42:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/u-k-gilts-reverse-decline-after-bank-of-england-minutes-release.html
U.K. government bonds reversed
declines after the release of the minutes of the most recent
 Bank of England  meeting showed policy makers considered adding
more stimulus to the economy.  The advance pushed down 10-year gilt yields by two basis
points to 2.37 percent. Two-year yields were also two basis
points lower, at 0.51 percent.  The nine-member Monetary Policy Committee, led by  Mervyn
King , voted 8-1 to maintain its asset-purchase plan at 200
billion pounds ($312 billion). Most policy makers said an
increse in the program is “increasingly probable.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark McCord at 
 mmccord2@bloomberg.net  